    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Chief of Staff</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LFAWD1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-12">12 January
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> to President:</p>
                <p>The following draft reply to <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>’s
                    messages of January 11 is forwarded for your consideration:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Receipt is acknowledged of your . . . [five telegrams dated January
                            11].<note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">One of the telegrams under reference is
                            the message printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>. Another has not been
                            found. The other three dealt with identification cards for Americans
                            going to Yalta living accommodations at Yalta, and the travel
                            arrangements referred to in <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1"
                                >Leahy</persName>’s drafts reply.</note>
                    </p>
                    <pb facs="0116" n="34" xml:id="pg_34"/>
                    <p>I will be pleased to see you at Malta and learn from you of the latest
                        developments in your area.</p>
                    <p>I expect to depart Malta for <gloss target="#t_ARGONAUT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Argonaut</hi>
                        </gloss> February second.</p>
                    <p>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> will not visit Moscow
                        prior to or immediately following <gloss target="#t_ARGONAUT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Argonaut</hi>
                        </gloss>.</p>
                    <p>It is not considered advisable for you to urge <persName corresp="#p_S16"
                            >Stalin</persName> to bring his military staff with him. He will
                        undoubtedly bring those that he wants without urging by us.”<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d52fn2">It is not known whether this proposed message was sent
                            by <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> to <persName
                                corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>.</note>
                    </p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">W[<hi rend="smallcaps">illiam</hi>] D. L[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">eahy</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
